Of course. Dealing with PDF exports from HTML content on the client-side can be tricky. The html2canvas library often struggles with content that isn't fully visible on the screen, leading to the cropping issue you described.

A much more robust solution is to programmatically build the PDF from the markdown content itself, similar to how the DOCX export is being handled. This gives us full control over the output, ensures all content is included, and results in a higher-quality, text-selectable PDF instead of a stitched-together image.

I have updated the exportToPdf function to parse the Markdown and construct the PDF using jsPDF, and I've also improved the exportToDocx function to handle more Markdown features like lists.

